01:03.730 --> 01:07.405
<i>(WOMAN) People have always
trusted me with their secrets,</i>

01:07.609 --> 01:11.159
<i>but who do I trust with mine?</i>

01:11.446 --> 01:14.950
<i>You. Only you.</i>

01:46.857 --> 01:49.656
<i>The first day of a new term.</i>

01:52.195 --> 01:55.449
Here come the local
pubescent proles,

01:55.574 --> 02:01.581
<i>the future plumbers and shop assistants
and doubtless the odd terrorist, too.</i>

02:04.249 --> 02:08.800
<i>In the old days, we confiscated
cigarettes and wank mags.</i>

02:08.878 --> 02:11.803
<i>Now it's knives and
crack cocaine.</i>

02:14.092 --> 02:16.641
<i>And they call it progress.</i>

02:20.724 --> 02:22.852
Tony.

02:23.060 --> 02:26.064
Mrs. Hart, art department.

02:26.229 --> 02:31.326
In 1517 Martin Luther nails his
95 points to a church door

02:31.443 --> 02:35.823
- in Wittenberg.
- (BELL RINGS)

02:39.284 --> 02:41.286
Poison granny.

02:46.833 --> 02:48.927
Piss off, you prick.

02:49.628 --> 02:53.678
Before we begin, for those of you
who haven't delivered your reports,

02:53.757 --> 02:57.978
please lob them in my general direction.
Thank you, Bill. Thank you, Mary.

02:58.095 --> 03:01.099
- Thank you, John. Thank you, Elaine.
- (DOOR OPENS)

03:01.765 --> 03:06.271
Ah. Has everyone met our
new art teacher, Sheba Hart?

03:06.353 --> 03:10.199
I've asked Sheba to sit in
on this meeting. As you all know,

03:10.273 --> 03:15.200
I regard the arts as absolutely essential
to our policy of reform through nurture.

03:15.278 --> 03:17.872
Thank you, Chris.
Very good. Very good.

03:18.115 --> 03:21.494
Thank you, Sue. I say,
that's a big one, isn't it?

03:21.576 --> 03:24.705
I'll be up till the crack of dawn!

03:24.788 --> 03:28.133
Anyone else not handed in
their homework? Right, and...

03:28.375 --> 03:30.093
Thank you.

03:30.711 --> 03:33.180
Lovely. Thank you.

03:34.339 --> 03:35.465
Barbara?

03:44.433 --> 03:47.687
This is your report?
On the history department?

03:47.769 --> 03:52.445
On its entire workings and your general
thoughts for its future development?

03:53.150 --> 03:55.824
You'll find it's quite thorough,
Headmaster.

03:57.696 --> 04:02.247
"The history department functions as one
would expect for a school of this intake.

04:02.325 --> 04:06.671
"Examination results have
been consistent for 30 years,

04:06.747 --> 04:10.627
"below the national average but
above the level of catastrophe."

04:11.334 --> 04:15.134
"Recommendation,
no change necessary."

04:18.091 --> 04:20.844
It took me most of the
summer to write it.

04:23.346 --> 04:25.940
<i>Hard to read the wispy novice.</i>

04:26.016 --> 04:27.939
Piss off, you prick.

04:28.018 --> 04:31.192
<i>Is she a sphinx,
or simply stupid?</i>

04:31.271 --> 04:34.491
All right. Off the phone, please.
Give me the phone.

04:34.566 --> 04:37.786
<i>Artfully dishevelled today.</i>

04:37.861 --> 04:40.740
<i>The tweedy tramp coat
is an abhorrence.</i>

04:40.822 --> 04:44.622
<i>It seems to say,
"I'm just like you."</i>

04:44.701 --> 04:47.454
<i>But clearly she's not.</i>

04:47.537 --> 04:50.541
<i>A fey person, I suspect.</i>

04:50.624 --> 04:52.501
<i>Fey.</i>

04:52.584 --> 04:55.463
(BOY) Come on, come on, pass it.
Yes, I'm over here!

04:55.545 --> 04:57.422
Yeah!

05:03.094 --> 05:05.517
- (BARBARA) Put your shirt on.
- I got the winner.

05:05.597 --> 05:08.396
Glory be. Shirt!

05:10.727 --> 05:15.358
<i>She has certainly rippled the
waters of our stagnant pond.</i>

05:15.440 --> 05:17.442
<i>They flock to her.</i>

05:17.526 --> 05:23.283
<i>Even limp little Brian had a go.
Oh, the horror.</i>

05:23.365 --> 05:25.914
- Hiya.
- Oh, hello.

05:25.992 --> 05:28.745
- That's a lovely blouse.
- What? Oh!

05:29.454 --> 05:32.173
<i>And Fatty Hodge has
pounced on her.</i>

05:32.249 --> 05:34.798
<i>A dubious double act,</i>

05:34.918 --> 05:38.047
<i>the blonde and the
pig in knickers.</i>

05:38.129 --> 05:41.474
I just went past the art studio.
It's like bloody <i>Lord of the Flies.</i>

05:41.591 --> 05:42.717
Have they gone for her?

05:42.801 --> 05:45.554
Torn her posters down.
There's a paint fight.

05:45.637 --> 05:49.938
They're chanting, "Get your tits out
for the lads." Girls, too. It's carnage.

05:50.100 --> 05:51.226
(MAN) How was madam?

05:51.309 --> 05:54.279
Lost it. "Stop it,
you little fucking bastards!"

05:54.604 --> 05:58.359
- You should have stepped in.
- He didn't want to patronise the lady.

05:58.441 --> 06:01.320
This time next year
she'll be headmistress.

06:01.403 --> 06:05.374
- Oh, Christ, will you shut up?
- Sorry. Sorry.

06:05.448 --> 06:08.372
Char, anyone?
Babs?

06:09.286 --> 06:12.665
- Milk, no sugar.
- Sweet enough?

06:12.747 --> 06:16.468
- Evidently.
- Didn't her father invent inflation?

06:16.751 --> 06:19.300
- You what?
- Wasn't her dad that academic?

06:19.546 --> 06:24.347
Donald whatsit. Economics bloke.
Invented the word "inflation".

06:24.551 --> 06:26.929
Oh, yeah.
I know who you mean.

06:27.304 --> 06:30.399
I think you'll find that Mrs.
Hart's father was Ronald Taylor.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.942
He didn't invent inflation.

06:33.393 --> 06:36.613
He devised a theory about
the relationship between inflation

06:36.771 --> 06:38.694
and consumer expectation.

06:44.905 --> 06:47.749
(SHEBA) Davis, get off him!
Stop it!

06:47.824 --> 06:51.169
- (BOY) No, you're an arsehole.
- (SHEBA) Stop it!

06:53.538 --> 06:56.848
(CHILDREN) Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight! Fight!

06:56.874 --> 06:59.320
Stop it! Stop it immediately!

06:59.377 --> 07:03.757
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!
Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight! Fight!

07:03.840 --> 07:07.185
(SHEBA) You're going to hurt
one another! Now, stop it!

07:07.344 --> 07:08.470
Davis, get off him!

07:09.179 --> 07:11.022
Enough!

07:11.181 --> 07:13.934
Outside! Now!

07:23.902 --> 07:27.702
- Fuck off!
- (BARBARA) Absolute silence. Absolute!

07:33.954 --> 07:37.925
- Why were they fighting, Mrs. Hart?
- Their motive was unclear.

07:37.999 --> 07:41.594
Davis, I know. You're a little thug.
Who might you be?

07:41.711 --> 07:43.429
- Steven Connolly, Miss.
- What?

07:43.588 --> 07:45.386
- Steven Connolly, Miss.
- Year?

07:45.548 --> 07:48.472
- Year 10, Miss.
- You're the naked footballer.

07:49.386 --> 07:53.232
Why were you fighting?
It's a perfectly simple question.

07:53.556 --> 07:55.854
- Dunno, Miss.
- You don't know.

07:56.101 --> 08:00.072
One minute you're inert, the next
you're trying to castrate a pupil.

08:00.313 --> 08:02.031
Nothing occurred
between these two states?

08:02.107 --> 08:03.199
No.

08:03.274 --> 08:06.494
Don't play the hero with me,
Connolly. Yes?

08:06.569 --> 08:09.573
Brain, mouth, speak.

08:11.366 --> 08:15.246
He was saying stuff about Miss.
It was bang out of order.

08:16.496 --> 08:19.295
- What did you say?
- I never said nothing, Miss.

08:19.541 --> 08:23.466
"I didn't say anything."
What did he say? Come on!

08:23.753 --> 08:26.927
He said she's a tart. He said he
gave her one up the arse.

08:27.340 --> 08:29.138
Did you, indeed?

08:29.384 --> 08:31.762
Odious boy. Apologise at once.

08:32.011 --> 08:35.482
- Sorry, Miss.
- (BARBARA) Deputy head in the morning.

08:35.890 --> 08:37.767
Get back inside, both of you.

08:43.606 --> 08:47.201
Little towers of testosterone.
You'll soon get used to them.

08:47.277 --> 08:50.451
Thank you so much.

08:50.530 --> 08:54.535
I'd better... Oh, I'm sorry. We
haven't met properly. I'm Sheba Hart.

08:54.617 --> 08:56.711
Barbara Covett.

08:59.664 --> 09:04.670
<i>Her voice is pure,
as if her mouth were empty and clean.</i>

09:04.753 --> 09:07.597
<i>As if she'd never had a filling.</i>

09:07.672 --> 09:10.926
<i>The complexion of a white peach.</i>

09:11.009 --> 09:13.728
<i>One can almost see her veins.</i>

09:14.095 --> 09:17.645
<i>Her trendy politics
are similarly transparent.</i>

09:17.891 --> 09:21.236
We serve them best if we teach
them to read, write and add.

09:21.311 --> 09:23.814
They don't need to know
about basket weavers.

09:23.897 --> 09:26.696
- Barbara's keen on the basics.
- When you started,

09:26.775 --> 09:29.369
didn't you want to give them
a real education

09:29.444 --> 09:33.790
to help them overcome
the poverty of their backgrounds?

09:33.865 --> 09:38.746
Oh, yes, of course. But one soon
learns that teaching is crowd control.

09:38.828 --> 09:41.377
Come here.
You know you're not supposed...

09:41.456 --> 09:46.508
We're a branch of the social services.
Put that back, you.

09:49.756 --> 09:51.599
Console yourself with the gems.

09:51.674 --> 09:55.099
That's when it's satisfying.
You can make a real difference.

09:55.178 --> 09:58.682
The rest is just
cattle-prod and pray.

09:59.849 --> 10:03.194
<i>I can see why others
are beguiled by her.</i>

10:04.270 --> 10:05.271
Oh, hello.

10:05.355 --> 10:09.155
<i>I wonder if she possesses
the requisite heft?</i>

10:09.234 --> 10:11.657
- Do you fancy a coffee?
- Yeah.

10:11.736 --> 10:13.784
- (SUE) Sheba!
- (PHONE BEEPS)

10:13.863 --> 10:14.464
Sorry.

10:14.490 --> 10:16.892
That's the year 11s.
They're a nightmare.

10:16.950 --> 10:19.874
Do you want to join us?
We're going for a quick coffee.

10:21.037 --> 10:25.417
- I've got a bit of an announcement.
- You're leaving St George's?

10:25.500 --> 10:26.968
No.

10:27.252 --> 10:29.880
Oh, you're pregnant.

10:33.007 --> 10:34.805
That's fantastic.

10:35.051 --> 10:38.305
Oh, congratulations.
When are you due?

10:38.388 --> 10:41.437
- June 7.
- A summer baby. How lovely.

10:41.516 --> 10:44.611
I can't believe nobody's noticed.
I'm 14 weeks.

10:44.686 --> 10:46.563
Didn't you see how
chunky I'm getting?

10:46.646 --> 10:48.990
Didn't like to say.
Where are you having it?

10:49.065 --> 10:52.820
(SUE) Homerton.
It's really nice there.

10:52.902 --> 10:55.030
Lovely, friendly nurses.

10:55.113 --> 10:58.037
I'm going to find out at the next scan.
20 weeks.

11:00.535 --> 11:04.961
- Do you want to come to lunch on Sunday?
- Where?

11:05.039 --> 11:08.384
To mine. To our house.

11:08.459 --> 11:12.839
- Won't you be with the family?
- Oh, yes, but you're very welcome.

11:12.922 --> 11:17.268
It's no big deal.
I'll just do a lasagne or something.

11:17.343 --> 11:19.471
I adore lasagne.

11:20.305 --> 11:26.654
<i>Bliss. A merry flag on the Arctic
wilderness of my calendar.</i>

11:26.728 --> 11:31.074
<i>One must make an effort
when one receives an invitation.</i>

11:33.234 --> 11:36.659
<i>The art of it is seeming not to.</i>

11:41.826 --> 11:45.547
<i>Lasagne tends to disagree with my bowels.</i>

11:45.622 --> 11:48.216
<i>I'll ask for a small portion.</i>

12:14.692 --> 12:17.240
Oh, I think I've got
the wrong house.

12:17.266 --> 12:20.349
No, you're bang on. I'm Richard.
Come in.

12:21.032 --> 12:22.750
I'm sorry. I thought...

12:22.825 --> 12:25.123
That I'd be 20 years younger
and handsome.

12:25.203 --> 12:27.422
- Bash!
- (SHEBA) The kitchen's on fire!

12:27.664 --> 12:30.258
Sorry if you were there long.
The bell's knackered.

12:30.500 --> 12:33.094
- Hi, Barbara.
- Hello.

12:36.047 --> 12:38.345
Oh, what a splendid room.

12:38.424 --> 12:41.769
What can I get you? We're semi-pro
drinkers here. You name it.

12:41.844 --> 12:43.938
(BARBARA) A dry sherry, please.

12:44.013 --> 12:48.018
I think we might have some
apricot brandy knocking around.

12:49.018 --> 12:50.270
- A dry white wine?
- Done.

12:50.395 --> 12:52.693
Have a seat.

13:00.822 --> 13:03.291
You must be Polly.
I'm Barbara.

13:03.366 --> 13:05.619
Hi, Barbara.

13:09.998 --> 13:13.002
- Are you going somewhere?
- Excuse me?

13:13.084 --> 13:15.963
- You're all poshed up.
- Oh.

13:16.045 --> 13:18.548
I have an appointment.

13:18.798 --> 13:21.267
Later, in town.

13:25.847 --> 13:30.648
- Have you always lived here?
- Mum inherited it. It's her little joke.

13:30.727 --> 13:34.402
I only married her for the property.
Morning.

13:35.606 --> 13:37.483
- Did Pete go?
- Mm.

13:37.567 --> 13:41.322
- He was welcome to stay.
- He's not really into lunch.

13:42.363 --> 13:43.785
Cheers.

13:45.616 --> 13:48.085
Mm.
Are you interested in wine?

13:48.161 --> 13:52.257
Only the drinking part.
You?

13:52.332 --> 13:55.552
- I spent the summer on the Amalfi coast...
- (BOY SHOUTING)

13:55.626 --> 14:00.257
Here's trouble. Now, now, now,
now, now, now, easy, Rocky! Easy.

14:00.506 --> 14:02.349
Easy, peasy. Wheezy.

14:02.592 --> 14:08.645
<i>I'd anticipated a suave young
lawyer and two perfect poppets.</i>

14:08.931 --> 14:13.277
<i>Not so. She's married
some crumbling patriarch.</i>

14:13.436 --> 14:15.313
<i>He's nearly as old as me.</i>

14:15.438 --> 14:19.659
<i>And then there's the daughter,
a pocket princess,</i>

14:19.734 --> 14:23.113
<i>and finally a somewhat tiresome
court jester.</i>

14:23.196 --> 14:26.871
Ah, lovely. Thank you.

14:28.076 --> 14:30.704
- I'm going to be a wizard.
- (BARBARA) Oh.

14:31.496 --> 14:35.342
- Is that when you're grown up?
- No. He's been cast in his school play.

14:35.416 --> 14:38.511
I'm gonna wear a
cape and my wand...

14:38.586 --> 14:43.808
Amongst next year's cultural highlights,
I greatly look forward to Benjamin Hart

14:43.883 --> 14:48.514
in the key role of "The Wizard", and I find
myself beside myself with anticipation.

14:48.596 --> 14:50.724
<i>A rogue image swam through me,</i>

14:50.807 --> 14:55.483
<i>hubby's pruney old mouth
pursed at Sheba's breast.</i>

14:55.853 --> 14:58.652
<i>( "FUNKY KINGSTON"
BY TOOTS AND THE MAYTALS)</i>

15:02.485 --> 15:06.490
<i>After lunch, a rather
mortifying family tradition.</i>

15:06.572 --> 15:10.827
<i>They do things differently
in bourgeois bohemia.</i>

15:21.045 --> 15:23.173
Oh! Thank you.

15:28.469 --> 15:31.222
Come on. Come on.

15:31.305 --> 15:33.399
No.

15:38.563 --> 15:40.565
(PHONE RINGS)

15:58.583 --> 16:00.335
- You ready?
- Watch out.

16:00.418 --> 16:02.637
Yes!

16:02.962 --> 16:05.082
He took me away for our anniversary.
It was years ago.

16:05.089 --> 16:07.717
When we came back it was here,

16:07.800 --> 16:09.393
as if by magic.

16:09.677 --> 16:12.226
Oh!

16:12.513 --> 16:15.813
It was supposed to
be my studio, but

16:17.101 --> 16:20.196
it's more of a refuge, really.

16:20.271 --> 16:22.569
A room of one's own.

16:24.650 --> 16:26.618
Is this you?

16:27.737 --> 16:29.080
(SHEBA) Mm.

16:29.238 --> 16:31.366
It was.

16:32.617 --> 16:35.245
Oh, I love these.

16:35.495 --> 16:36.710
Such vibrant colours.

16:36.736 --> 16:39.570
Take one. Take two.
Have the lot, actually.

16:39.624 --> 16:44.346
- I couldn't possibly.
- Honestly, no one else wants them.

16:44.420 --> 16:47.390
I'll treasure them.

16:47.465 --> 16:51.561
It must be exhausting, running
a family and teaching as well.

16:51.636 --> 16:55.061
Oh, I can't wait for
term to end.

16:55.139 --> 16:58.769
Roll on Christmas and
a month of sod all.

17:02.313 --> 17:06.113
I shouldn't have kidded
myself I could teach.

17:06.817 --> 17:10.946
It's just that I've spent the
last ten years looking after Ben

17:11.030 --> 17:13.874
and I was so desperate
to get out and do something,

17:13.950 --> 17:19.127
and finally we get him into this great
local school and I'm free to work and...

17:20.080 --> 17:24.382
- You're gonna be a terrific teacher.
- Thanks.

17:24.961 --> 17:28.966
But I'm bloody hopeless,
and everyone knows it.

17:29.090 --> 17:31.138
Children are feral.

17:31.300 --> 17:34.144
Don't let them sense
your anxiety.

17:36.472 --> 17:39.851
- How do you cope?
- Oh, I'm just a battle-axe.

17:40.476 --> 17:42.979
I'm not popular,
but they respect me.

17:43.396 --> 17:48.277
Well, you're popular with me. It's
strange. I feel like I can talk to you.

17:48.484 --> 17:51.283
<i>She spoke of her vile mother,</i>

17:52.154 --> 17:55.704
<i>her grief over the
death of her father,</i>

17:55.992 --> 17:58.996
<i>the glory days when
Richard scooped her up</i>

17:59.161 --> 18:05.168
<i>and then jettisoned wife and children
for what she called a nonstop fuckfest.</i>

18:06.168 --> 18:12.346
<i>It's a peculiar trait of the privileged,
immediate incautious intimacy.</i>

18:12.967 --> 18:17.063
<i>But Sheba went well beyond
the tendencies of her class.</i>

18:18.014 --> 18:20.688
<i>She was utterly candid,</i>

18:21.726 --> 18:25.026
<i>a novice confessing to
the mother superior.</i>

18:25.855 --> 18:30.076
You know, marriage and kids,
I mean, it's wonderful,

18:30.151 --> 18:33.405
but it doesn't give you meaning.

18:33.654 --> 18:37.284
It gives you an imperative
but it doesn't help you...

18:37.366 --> 18:42.213
My father always used to say,
you know, on the tube, "Mind the gap."

18:45.458 --> 18:51.090
I don't know. It's just the distance
between life as you dream it

18:51.172 --> 18:53.266
and

18:54.717 --> 18:56.936
life as it is.

18:59.722 --> 19:02.145
I know exactly what you mean.

19:09.565 --> 19:12.034
A gold-star day.

19:13.402 --> 19:16.576
<i>I always knew we'd be friends.</i>

19:16.947 --> 19:19.041
<i>Our mutual reserve inhibited us,</i>

19:19.116 --> 19:23.792
<i>but now it is manifest,
a spiritual recognition.</i>

19:25.164 --> 19:27.917
(HEADMASTER) Many of you
will enjoy Christmas.

19:28.084 --> 19:31.088
<i>S and I share the ability</i>

19:31.253 --> 19:35.975
<i>to see through the quotidian
awfulness of things.</i>

19:37.885 --> 19:40.764
<i>In a different, better age,</i>

19:40.846 --> 19:43.941
<i>we would be ladies of leisure,
lunching together,</i>

19:44.016 --> 19:46.690
<i>visiting galleries, travelling,</i>

19:46.769 --> 19:49.067
<i>putting the world to rights.</i>

19:49.146 --> 19:52.946
<i>We would be companions.</i>

19:59.323 --> 20:02.998
<i>Christ by highest heaven adored</i>

20:03.077 --> 20:06.547
<i>Christ the everlasting Lord</i>

20:06.622 --> 20:09.592
<i>Late in time behold him come</i>

20:09.667 --> 20:12.921
<i>Offspring of a virgin's womb</i>

20:13.003 --> 20:16.223
It's taken.
I'm saving it for Sheba.

20:16.340 --> 20:17.466
Sorry.

20:17.550 --> 20:19.644
<i>Hail the incarnate Deity</i>

20:20.219 --> 20:22.847
<i>Pleased as man with man to dwell</i>

20:22.930 --> 20:26.434
<i>Jesus, Emmanuel</i>

20:26.517 --> 20:29.737
<i>Hark! The herald angels sing</i>

20:29.812 --> 20:34.363
<i>Glory to the newborn King</i>

20:36.444 --> 20:37.787
(WHISPERS)

21:31.081 --> 21:33.504
Very good.
Well done.

21:51.060 --> 21:53.154
<i>(BOYS) Hark!
The herald angels sing</i>

21:53.229 --> 21:56.073
<i>"Glory to the newborn King"</i>

21:56.148 --> 21:58.492
<i>Hark! The herald angels sing</i>

21:58.567 --> 22:01.491
<i>"Glory to the newborn King"</i>

22:01.570 --> 22:03.993
<i>Hark!
The herald angels sing</i>

22:04.073 --> 22:07.623
<i>Glory to the newborn King</i>

22:40.442 --> 22:42.444
(PHONE RINGS)

22:44.280 --> 22:46.453
Ben, pop it in the car,
sweetheart. Hello?

22:47.032 --> 22:49.751
I need to speak to you
about Steven Connolly.

22:51.287 --> 22:54.040
- Who?
- Let's not, shall we?

22:54.456 --> 22:58.256
<i>Doubtless you're aware
you've committed a criminal of fence.</i>

22:58.586 --> 23:00.964
<i>I'll be with you at five.</i>

23:05.426 --> 23:07.053
Let's go to the pub, OK?

23:10.264 --> 23:12.858
When will you tell them?

23:13.100 --> 23:15.478
I need to know the circumstances.

23:15.769 --> 23:18.147
You must inform me of everything.

23:21.233 --> 23:24.407
Actually, you were there
when I first saw him.

23:24.737 --> 23:27.206
<i>I think you gave him a telling off.</i>

23:27.489 --> 23:30.333
(BARBARA)
<i>I gave him a slight ticking off.</i>

23:30.659 --> 23:33.162
<i>(SHEBA)
He dedicated his goal to me.</i>

23:33.621 --> 23:36.340
It amused me, nothing more.

23:37.625 --> 23:42.131
Then a few days later he
came to see me.

23:42.504 --> 23:44.783
Would you have a
look at me drawings?

23:44.809 --> 23:47.626
I'll look in class.
You do Art, don't you?

23:48.010 --> 23:50.934
I'm not allowed.
I'm special needs.

23:51.347 --> 23:54.100
I gotta do extra reading instead.

23:54.350 --> 23:56.853
Did you do these at home?

24:05.527 --> 24:07.950
These are good.

24:08.364 --> 24:10.332
You can draw.

24:13.285 --> 24:16.835
If we pull strings for one child
the whole system will unravel.

24:16.914 --> 24:20.259
But he's talented.
He's found something he believes in.

24:20.334 --> 24:22.462
Well, they're all talented.

24:23.212 --> 24:26.432
You found your gem,
as Sue would say.

24:26.507 --> 24:31.354
I said that I would teach him after
school, but only if he felt like it.

24:31.428 --> 24:35.478
- It's our job, isn't it?
- Within specified hours and curriculum.

24:35.557 --> 24:39.312
Barbara, he came every
day for two weeks.

24:40.270 --> 24:43.490
Yes, I was flattered,
but more than that.

24:43.565 --> 24:47.069
<i>I was excited to find someone
who wanted to learn.</i>

24:47.152 --> 24:53.376
And he imagined this sort of helicopter
500 years ago. it does your brain in.

24:53.450 --> 24:56.795
<i>(BARBARA) But surely you must have
suspected his motives?</i>

24:56.870 --> 25:01.717
I sensed he had a little crush
on me, but so what?

25:01.792 --> 25:03.886
It was innocent.

25:03.961 --> 25:07.215
That's so much better.
You've absolutely got that knuckle.

25:07.297 --> 25:09.391
Nailed it.

25:11.176 --> 25:15.431
- Do that again, Miss.
- Don't be silly. Off you go.

25:16.807 --> 25:21.404
- What are you having for tea, Miss?
- Probably buy something on the way home.

25:21.478 --> 25:23.572
- Are you a good cook?
- Not really.

25:23.647 --> 25:25.741
You suck?

25:29.361 --> 25:31.989
Go home, Steven.

25:42.291 --> 25:45.716
- That's when you should have stopped it.
- I did.

25:45.794 --> 25:47.967
I told him I wouldn't
teach him any more.

25:48.047 --> 25:51.176
But he refused to accept it.
He just kept coming back.

25:53.469 --> 25:55.563
Miss!

25:57.389 --> 25:59.733
<i>(SHEBA) It began to feel
like our secret,</i>

25:59.808 --> 26:04.609
<i>and secrets can be seductive.</i>

26:15.324 --> 26:19.170
- D'you wanna come for a walk?
- Absolutely not.

26:19.787 --> 26:23.041
I'm going home to my family.
As should you.

26:23.123 --> 26:25.171
Miss!

26:28.337 --> 26:32.558
My dad's got the sack.
He's been taking it out on me.

26:32.633 --> 26:36.638
<i>(SHEBA) His father hit him. He didn't
tell his mum because she was ill.</i>

26:36.720 --> 26:40.770
<i>- Does your mother know?
- Kidney disease.</i>

26:40.849 --> 26:44.774
- It's taking months for an operation.
- He was so vulnerable.

26:44.853 --> 26:47.652
If he does it again, you tell me.

26:47.898 --> 26:50.071
Thanks, Miss.

26:51.068 --> 26:53.116
You're beautiful, Miss.

26:53.195 --> 26:54.947
You don't know how
beautiful you are.

27:02.204 --> 27:06.254
<i>(SHEBA) I hadn't been pursued
like this for years.</i>

27:06.333 --> 27:11.214
<i>I knew it was wrong and immoral
and completely ridiculous,</i>

27:11.296 --> 27:14.015
but I don't know.

27:14.091 --> 27:16.640
I just allowed it to happen.

27:16.718 --> 27:18.766
The boy is 15!

27:21.306 --> 27:25.277
- But he's quite mature for his age.
- "But" is not a helpful word here.

27:26.854 --> 27:29.357
This is going to sound sick

27:30.774 --> 27:37.202
but something in me felt entitled. You
know, I've been good all my adult life.

27:37.281 --> 27:41.787
I've been a decent wife,
dutiful mother, coping with Ben.

27:42.536 --> 27:46.666
<i>This voice inside me kept saying,
"Why shouldn't you be bad?</i>

27:46.748 --> 27:50.969
<i>"You know, why shouldn't you transgress?
You've earned the right."</i>

27:51.044 --> 27:52.546
I said get out, Denzel.

27:52.629 --> 27:57.055
The rest of you get on
with your work, please.

27:57.134 --> 27:59.432
Hurry up.

28:11.106 --> 28:13.108
(BEN LAUGHS)

28:26.622 --> 28:29.876
Sue phoned.
OK if I meet her for a drink?

28:30.751 --> 28:33.675
Sure.
I'll put bug-a-lugs to bed.

28:48.227 --> 28:50.321
Evening, Miss.

29:21.343 --> 29:23.641
Make yourself comfortable.

29:23.720 --> 29:27.816
It's incredibly important
we keep this secret.

29:30.852 --> 29:33.981
- Does anyone know you're here?
- No.

29:38.485 --> 29:40.487
Miss.

29:40.570 --> 29:43.540
I'm no genius,
but I ain't a dickhead.

29:44.283 --> 29:46.206
I won't tell no one.

29:46.535 --> 29:48.788
You can trust me.

29:51.581 --> 29:54.801
We'd both get into
terrible trouble.

30:19.192 --> 30:22.492
It was easy,
like having another drink

30:22.571 --> 30:25.450
when you know you shouldn't.

30:28.577 --> 30:30.830
Can I smoke, Miss?

30:31.079 --> 30:35.425
You can do what you want,
but enough of this "Miss".

30:45.344 --> 30:47.767
Were you a model once?

30:49.348 --> 30:52.477
Well, you should have been.
You're well fit.

30:52.893 --> 30:55.021
Gosh, but don't I know it.

30:55.228 --> 30:57.526
You're into The Streets?

30:58.106 --> 31:00.359
Well, my daughter is.

31:01.485 --> 31:04.284
Is she the same age as me?

31:04.488 --> 31:06.661
None of your beeswax.

31:11.453 --> 31:14.798
Well, anyway,
the point is you're fit.

31:17.292 --> 31:19.545
Well, so are you.

31:19.795 --> 31:25.177
You reckon? My sister thinks
I look like a bollock with measles.

31:27.010 --> 31:29.479
You've done my brain in.

31:59.668 --> 32:02.638
- You wanna do it again?
- (LAUGHS)

32:04.172 --> 32:06.015
What?

32:08.218 --> 32:10.186
Yes.

32:10.929 --> 32:13.057
I wanna do it again.

32:16.685 --> 32:19.029
I wanna do it again.

32:20.689 --> 32:22.942
The day we met,

32:23.775 --> 32:25.322
it had already begun?

32:27.362 --> 32:28.909
Yes.

32:28.989 --> 32:31.492
Deputy head in the morning.

32:31.575 --> 32:35.751
Noble sentiment, Connolly.
Next time, words, not fists.

32:35.829 --> 32:37.957
Get inside, both of you.

32:38.039 --> 32:44.513
- And you had further relations that day?
- We went to the art room.

32:44.588 --> 32:48.218
Well, I'm glad I was such an aphrodisiac.
I was trying to help you.

32:48.300 --> 32:51.349
You did. I'm incredibly grateful.

32:51.428 --> 32:54.227
You've been such a good friend.

32:55.724 --> 32:58.193
Not reciprocated, it seems.

33:01.938 --> 33:05.067
I desperately wanted
to confess to you.

33:06.067 --> 33:07.910
But how could I?

33:08.778 --> 33:10.280
Barbara?

33:10.572 --> 33:14.076
It would have put you
in an impossible situation.

33:16.328 --> 33:18.706
I so wish I had.

33:18.914 --> 33:21.713
You would have made me see sense.

33:22.042 --> 33:25.592
<i>(BARBARA) And then I realised
my fury had blinded me.</i>

33:26.421 --> 33:29.925
<i>There was a magnificent
opportunity here.</i>

33:30.258 --> 33:33.353
<i>Can we go inside?
I'm absolutely freezing.</i>

33:36.431 --> 33:41.028
<i>With stealth, I might secure
the prize long term,</i>

33:41.102 --> 33:44.231
<i>forever in my debt.</i>

33:44.689 --> 33:47.943
<i>I could gain everything</i>

33:48.318 --> 33:50.412
<i>by doing nothing.</i>

33:52.864 --> 33:54.958
Look...

33:56.535 --> 34:01.416
I know you have to tell them.
You know, the head, the school.

34:01.790 --> 34:05.044
All I ask is that you wait
till the New Year.

34:06.169 --> 34:10.424
I'm begging you. Please let me have
this Christmas with my family.

34:10.632 --> 34:13.931
Oh, you poor thing.

34:14.969 --> 34:17.143
You've got yourself into a state?

34:18.598 --> 34:20.565
I'm not going to report you.

34:21.434 --> 34:25.484
I want to help you,
to support you through this.

34:30.360 --> 34:33.079
You're not going to tell?

34:35.364 --> 34:37.833
- You won't tell anyone?
- Who would it benefit?

34:37.993 --> 34:41.418
Not you or the boy,
and certainly not the school.

34:42.038 --> 34:44.291
No, this is a private matter,

34:45.125 --> 34:48.049
and we must keep it so.

34:49.337 --> 34:50.929
Yes.

34:56.386 --> 34:58.514
- Maybe I should resign.
- Oh, no.

34:58.597 --> 35:00.691
No, that might alert suspicion.

35:00.765 --> 35:06.067
No, you must stay at the school,
but the affair must end.

35:06.313 --> 35:08.657
Your solemn promise.

35:10.859 --> 35:13.328
I can't help you if
you don't promise.

35:14.446 --> 35:16.448
I promise.

35:19.367 --> 35:22.337
So you'll tell him straight
after Christmas?

35:22.412 --> 35:25.086
- It's all for the best.
- I know.

35:25.165 --> 35:29.261
Thank you so much.
You've been so brilliant.

35:29.336 --> 35:32.089
And you'll tell me
when it's done?

35:36.593 --> 35:39.142
Oh! You never said.

35:39.429 --> 35:42.182
- (BARBARA) Standard issue for spinsters.
- (LAUGHS)

35:42.849 --> 35:45.477
She's been off her food.
I'm worried about her.

35:45.560 --> 35:49.235
There's a terrific vet up the road.
He was great with Ben's rabbit.

35:49.689 --> 35:51.856
Got many people coming tomorrow?

35:51.882 --> 35:55.266
My lot, Richard's lot,
including first wife.

35:55.487 --> 35:57.831
Oh. And your mother?

35:58.239 --> 36:00.162
Oh, yes.

36:00.241 --> 36:02.994
- Well, happy Christmas.
- Yeah. You, too.

36:03.078 --> 36:05.627
Thank you so much.

36:05.789 --> 36:07.416
Courage, mon brave.

36:07.582 --> 36:12.053
<i>And bon voyage to
her little leprechaun.</i>

36:14.422 --> 36:18.518
<i>Sheba and I share
a deep understanding now.</i>

36:20.679 --> 36:22.932
<i>No one can violate</i>

36:23.014 --> 36:25.608
<i>our magnificent complicity.</i>

36:25.767 --> 36:28.691
No! Wait till tomorrow!
Stop.

36:30.480 --> 36:32.608
You've been gone ages.

36:32.816 --> 36:34.113
Oh.

36:34.317 --> 36:37.161
Barbara was a little...
Some school thing.

36:37.445 --> 36:40.289
- How's his nibs?
- Oh, still awake.

36:40.615 --> 36:44.119
He's madly excited.
I said he could stay up for you.

36:44.577 --> 36:45.749
And Polly?

36:46.913 --> 36:48.631
- Depressed.
- Oh.

36:48.790 --> 36:50.588
Pete phoned.

36:50.875 --> 36:52.718
They had a row

36:53.044 --> 36:55.388
and he's not coming tomorrow.

36:56.381 --> 36:58.267
D'you think he's bad news?

36:58.293 --> 37:01.628
Well, these older men
can be very dodgy.

37:16.317 --> 37:18.160
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

37:19.028 --> 37:21.326
Did Daddy tell you?

37:24.409 --> 37:28.255
He's gonna bin me, I know it.

37:28.329 --> 37:30.423
You're very lovely, darling.

37:30.498 --> 37:33.593
He's clever enough
to appreciate it.

37:33.668 --> 37:36.137
I'm fat as fuck, Mum.

37:38.256 --> 37:40.725
He'll be back.

37:41.009 --> 37:43.011
I can't live without him.

37:43.303 --> 37:45.397
Oh...

37:47.557 --> 37:51.778
<i>Her fetish for the boy was
simply her snobbery manifested.</i>

37:51.853 --> 37:54.197
<i>He's working class
and he likes art,</i>

37:54.272 --> 37:57.446
<i>as if he were a monkey who just
strolled out of a rainforest</i>

37:57.525 --> 38:00.995
<i>and asked for a gin and tonic.</i>

38:05.700 --> 38:09.295
Have you heard from
that friend of yours, Barbara?

38:09.370 --> 38:12.670
Bar? Wakey-wakey.

38:12.749 --> 38:16.595
Lorraine was asking if you'd heard
from that nice friend of yours.

38:16.669 --> 38:18.763
- Who?
- Jennifer Dodd.

38:20.340 --> 38:21.592
Oh.

38:21.674 --> 38:24.427
She left the school.

38:24.511 --> 38:27.139
She's teaching in a
primary at Stoke.

38:27.889 --> 38:32.486
There's a chap, apparently.
I heard they're engaged.

38:36.189 --> 38:38.317
But it's true, it would be insane,
wouldn't it?

38:38.399 --> 38:41.403
It's the most ridiculous
time for him to sell.

38:41.486 --> 38:43.989
Well, that's what I said.

38:44.239 --> 38:46.207
I know.
He should give me a ring.

38:46.282 --> 38:49.081
It's absolute madness
for him. I'm happy to...

38:49.160 --> 38:51.128
(SHEBA) There you are, darling.

38:51.204 --> 38:54.959
...Victorian parent or something.
I'm nothing of the kind!

38:55.041 --> 38:58.295
Darling, can we have gravy?
There's no gravy. Sorry.

38:58.378 --> 39:00.972
Why can't we just have...

39:02.257 --> 39:04.259
(PHONE BEEPS)

39:27.282 --> 39:30.126
(WOMAN) God knows.
But this is what she's like.

39:30.201 --> 39:34.581
Ever since Ronald died,
she's drifted inexorably.

39:34.664 --> 39:39.511
You see, her father was
an exceptional man. Exceptional.

39:39.919 --> 39:42.047
Bathsheba's a loner,
I'm afraid.

39:42.130 --> 39:45.851
She's beautiful, thank God,
and it's got her through,

39:45.925 --> 39:49.930
but it's not quite the same
as possessing substance.

39:58.271 --> 39:59.443
Happy Christmas.

39:59.522 --> 40:02.196
What are you doing here?
Everyone's inside.

40:02.442 --> 40:05.036
Aren't you gonna open it?

40:09.991 --> 40:13.120
It's made of real fake gold.

40:16.497 --> 40:19.091
- Thank you.
- What's up?

40:19.500 --> 40:21.594
I haven't heard from you.

40:25.632 --> 40:27.851
I can't see you any more.

40:28.718 --> 40:30.686
I'm sorry. I...

40:31.846 --> 40:33.769
- I just can't. It's over.
- (DOOR OPENS)

40:35.058 --> 40:38.028
- Why?
- (RICHARD) Bash?

40:38.102 --> 40:39.399
Bash!

40:40.063 --> 40:41.815
She's not here.

40:46.319 --> 40:48.538
Was that your dad?

40:50.531 --> 40:51.874
No.

40:51.950 --> 40:54.044
He's an uncle.

40:56.788 --> 41:00.838
- Do you wanna end it?
- Please don't look at me like that.

41:00.917 --> 41:03.386
- Have you gone off me?
- No.

41:04.671 --> 41:08.141
You should go.
Please, don't make...

41:08.967 --> 41:10.765
Just go.

41:31.197 --> 41:33.495
(POLLY) She gave me what?
(LAUGHS)

41:33.574 --> 41:37.044
- What colour are they?
- (SHEBA) Is it Pete?

41:51.092 --> 41:53.094
(SOBS)

42:01.811 --> 42:05.486
<i>I long to phone S,
but it's late.</i>

42:06.858 --> 42:11.034
<i>Poor girl, all alone
with her awful family.</i>

42:12.071 --> 42:16.201
<i>Our lives are acutely similar
in so many respects.</i>

42:16.409 --> 42:19.083
- (KNOCK AT DOOR)
- (WOMAN) Sis?

42:21.873 --> 42:23.841
Oh.

42:23.916 --> 42:27.716
Writing the old diary?
I can't imagine how you keep at it.

42:27.795 --> 42:30.093
I'd have nothing to say.

42:31.841 --> 42:33.843
- (CAT MEOWS)
- Aw.

42:35.261 --> 42:37.605
Hello.

42:37.805 --> 42:42.436
You know you're welcome whenever
you want, not just once a year.

42:43.728 --> 42:47.107
It's just that I'm rather
busy at the moment.

42:47.273 --> 42:49.992
Your racy London life.

42:50.151 --> 42:52.449
I'm glad it's so full.

42:56.282 --> 43:00.037
I'm sorry about Jennifer.
She was lovely.

43:02.330 --> 43:06.585
Is there anyone else?
Someone else who's special?

43:07.668 --> 43:09.841
I don't know what you mean.

43:10.171 --> 43:12.594
I... I didn't mean to pry.

43:16.427 --> 43:18.429
(SHEBA MOANING)

43:33.486 --> 43:34.829
Belated Christmas present.

43:35.613 --> 43:37.536
Oh, thank you.

43:40.451 --> 43:42.328
Oh, my word.

43:42.995 --> 43:44.793
Asprey.

43:58.553 --> 44:01.227
How is she?

44:03.224 --> 44:05.727
You are the most wonderful friend.

44:22.285 --> 44:24.708
Any good?

44:26.497 --> 44:28.591
It's a masterpiece.

44:30.042 --> 44:32.795
Don't they teach you anything?

44:46.392 --> 44:48.645
We used to worship her.

44:57.987 --> 45:00.456
- Take it off.
- What's it for?

45:00.698 --> 45:03.952
Just take it off, please.
I'm still making it.

45:04.035 --> 45:06.129
Yeah, but why?

45:07.371 --> 45:10.295
- It's for my son.
- But he's 12, isn't he?

45:10.374 --> 45:13.423
He's got Dawn's syndrome.

45:17.423 --> 45:19.471
You never said.

45:21.928 --> 45:23.646
Right.

45:25.223 --> 45:27.317
Sorry.

45:38.569 --> 45:39.741
(CAT RETCHES)

45:39.820 --> 45:41.618
Oh...

45:41.822 --> 45:43.870
Oh.

45:44.575 --> 45:47.375
(MAN) I'm sure she's
had a very happy life.

45:47.401 --> 45:48.355
Well, yes.

45:48.412 --> 45:51.382
She has. Thank you.

45:51.457 --> 45:54.427
We can make her more comfortable
for the next few weeks,

45:54.502 --> 45:57.676
but it will be weeks
rather than months.

45:58.798 --> 46:01.392
You've had a terrible shock.

46:03.344 --> 46:06.143
Where's Richard?
I don't want to disturb you.

46:06.347 --> 46:09.817
- It's fine. Everyone's out.
- (PHONE RINGS)

46:09.892 --> 46:11.894
(ENDS CALL)

46:13.479 --> 46:15.857
Can they treat her?

46:16.232 --> 46:19.281
He says it's just a
matter of weeks.

46:21.195 --> 46:23.448
- She's only a pet.
- Oh, no.

46:23.531 --> 46:26.410
I cried for weeks
when our dog died. Weeks.

46:26.492 --> 46:28.870
One does get so attached.

46:40.214 --> 46:42.558
I should leave you in peace.

46:44.427 --> 46:46.521
Yeah.

46:56.480 --> 46:59.575
- I like that top. It suits you.
- Oh. Thanks.

46:59.650 --> 47:01.652
(PHONE BEEPS)

47:04.238 --> 47:06.912
When I was at school

47:07.241 --> 47:12.088
if one of us had had some
bad news or was a bit down,

47:12.913 --> 47:14.915
we used to stroke each other.

47:15.249 --> 47:20.426
You know, someone would do one arm
and someone else the other.

47:22.048 --> 47:24.267
It was a wonderful sensation.

47:24.425 --> 47:26.393
Did you do that at your school?

47:27.470 --> 47:29.097
No.

47:29.347 --> 47:32.021
It's incredibly relaxing

47:33.434 --> 47:36.233
for the giver and the receiver.

47:43.110 --> 47:45.579
- Close your eyes. No, no, really.
- Oh...

47:45.654 --> 47:48.157
It doesn't work if you don't.

48:26.404 --> 48:28.998
- There's a good girl.
- That's enough.

48:29.115 --> 48:30.366
No, close your eyes.

48:30.392 --> 48:33.520
Look, I really think
that's enough, Barbara.

48:41.919 --> 48:44.968
There's someone in your garden!
He came over the wall.

48:45.047 --> 48:48.176
It's probably the neighbour's boy,
lost his football.

48:48.259 --> 48:50.105
No, he's going into
the summer house!

48:50.131 --> 48:52.414
It's just a kid from next door.
Forget it.

48:52.763 --> 48:54.891
(PHONE RINGS)

49:01.522 --> 49:06.323
